# WIP-a-Snapper v1.0.2 - User Guide

## üì∏ Overview

**WIP-a-Snapper** is a professional After Effects composition screenshot tool designed to streamline your workflow-in-progress documentation. It automatically generates organized, timestamped screenshots with intelligent naming conventions and flexible save locations.

## ‚ú® Key Features

- **üéØ One-Click Screenshots** - Capture the current frame from any composition
- **üè∑Ô∏è Smart Naming** - Automatic file naming with project and composition details
- **üìÅ Flexible Storage** - Save to custom locations or project root folders
- **‚öôÔ∏è Customizable Settings** - Persistent preferences for naming and save locations
- **üìä Progress Tracking** - Visual feedback during screenshot capture
- **üîÑ Auto-Incrementing** - Never overwrite existing screenshots
- **üíæ Project Integration** - Seamlessly works with your After Effects workflow

## üöÄ Quick Start

### 1. Installation
1. Copy the `wip-a-snapper_v1.0.2.jsx` file to your After Effects Scripts folder
2. Restart After Effects
3. Navigate to **File > Scripts > Run Script File...** and select the script

### 2. First Use
1. Open a composition in After Effects
2. Position the playhead at the desired frame
3. Click **"Take Screenshot"** to capture the current frame

## üéõÔ∏è Interface Overview

### Main Controls
- **Naming Convention Dropdown** - Choose how files are named
- **Settings Button** - Configure save location and preferences
- **Take Screenshot Button** - Capture the current frame
- **Progress Bar** - Shows screenshot capture progress
- **Status Text** - Displays current operation status

### Naming Convention Options
1. **Project & Comp Name** (Default) - `ProjectName_CompName_-001-v1.0.png`
2. **Project Name Only** - `ProjectName_-001-v1.0.png`
3. **Comp Name Only** - `CompName_-001-v1.0.png`

## ‚öôÔ∏è Configuration

### Save Location Settings
1. Click the **"Settings"** button
2. Choose between:
   - **Custom Location** - Set a specific folder for all screenshots
   - **Project Root** - Hold Shift while clicking "Take Screenshot" to save in `_WIP-a-Snapper` folder

### Custom Save Location
1. Open Settings dialog
2. Click **"Browse"** to select a folder
3. Click **"OK"** to save your preference
4. Your choice is remembered between sessions

## üì± Usage Instructions

### Basic Screenshot
1. **Select Composition** - Make sure your desired composition is active
2. **Position Playhead** - Move to the exact frame you want to capture
3. **Click "Take Screenshot"** - The script will automatically:
   - Check composition resolution
   - Generate appropriate filename
   - Save as PNG format
   - Provide confirmation

### Shift-Click for Project Root
- Hold **Shift** while clicking "Take Screenshot"
- Saves to `_WIP-a-Snapper` folder in your project directory
- Useful for project-specific documentation

### Resolution Warnings
The script automatically detects if your composition is set to less than Full resolution and warns you about potential quality loss.

## üìÅ File Organization

### Automatic Folder Creation
- **Custom Location**: Creates project-named subfolders automatically
- **Project Root**: Creates `_WIP-a-Snapper` folder if it doesn't exist

### File Naming Examples
```
Project_v1.0_Intro_-001-v1.0.png
Project_v1.0_Intro_-002-v1.0.png
Project_v1.0_Intro_-003-v1.0.png
```

### Auto-Incrementing
- Files are automatically numbered (001, 002, 003, etc.)
- Never overwrites existing files
- Supports up to 999 screenshots per project

## üîß Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

**"Please select a composition"**
- Make sure a composition is active in After Effects
- Check that you're in the Composition panel, not Project panel

**"Please save your After Effects project"**
- Save your project with a proper name first
- Or use Shift+Click to save in project root

**"Save location folder not found"**
- Check your Settings configuration
- Verify the folder path still exists
- Re-configure in Settings if needed

**Low-quality screenshots**
- Ensure composition is set to Full resolution
- Check the resolution warning dialog

### Error Recovery
- Check the progress bar and status text for operation details
- Verify file permissions in your save location
- Ensure sufficient disk space

## üí° Pro Tips

### Workflow Integration
